(53, 'Starter Kits', 'Sensor Based Projects', 'Arduino/AVR Projects', 'Simple Electronics Projects', 'Elecduino Trios', 1999, 1999, '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>WHAT IS ELECDUINO?</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The elecduino kit is a great way to get started with electronics. The elecduino kit which comes in many variants lets you make many different projects which helps you gain the practical knowledge of the components you have only studied in theory.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>HOW IT WILL HELP YOU?</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This kit will increase your efficiency of self-learning and can save a lot of time and money by the cutting the cost and time on specialized training. Our team has designed several services with the kit that will ease down every process.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Trios, elecduino', 'kit2.jpeg', 'Elecbits_Elecduino53.doc', 'block53.PNG', '<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>HARDWARE:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Project Book</li>\r\n<li>Arduino UNO R3</li>\r\n<li>Breadboard</li>\r\n<li>Pushbuttons</li>\r\n<li>Blue leds (5mm)</li>\r\n<li>Yellow/Orange leds (5mm)</li>\r\n<li>Green leds (5mm)</li>\r\n<li>Red leds (5mm)</li>\r\n<li>NPN Transistors</li>\r\n<li>Diodes 1N4007</li>\r\n<li>Resistors Multivalues</li>\r\n<li>Ceramic capacitors multivalues</li>\r\n<li>9V Battery with snap</li>\r\n<li>Male to male jumper wires</li>\r\n<li>Female to female jumper wires</li>\r\n<li>Buzzer</li>\r\n<li>Phototransistors</li>\r\n<li>Potentiometer 10k ohm</li>\r\n<li>Temperature sensor</li>\r\n<li>Seven segment display</li>\r\n<li>DC Motor</li>\r\n<li>Shift registers</li>\r\n<li>Servo motor</li>\r\n<li>Keypad 4*4</li>\r\n<li>16*2 LCD Display</li>\r\n<li>Ultrasonic Distance Sensor</li>\r\n<li>Tilt Switch</li>\r\n<li>Touchscreen</li>\r\n<li>PIR Sensor</li>\r\n<li>MQ Gas sensor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>SOFTWARE:</st